    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Different versions of the bellflower toolbelt are customized to appear to suit specific trades, so a belt used for carpentry would look different from a belt for baking.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong><span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> envision, Interact</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You place an object of up to 1 Bulk into the belt, transforming that object into a tool befitting the trade for which the belt was created. Each object remains transformed until it has been removed from the belt for 24 hours or someone uses a single Interact action to return it to its normal form. If enough transformed items are in it, the belt can be used as @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.y34yjumCFakrbtdw]{Artisan's Tools} for that trade.</p>"
